{
  "stem": "15694.9",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But when I got this food, he took it from the bottom.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was thick stuff.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it helped us, but it wasn't enough.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now, having mentioned a half a ration of bread, I better tell you what a ration was.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "A ration was, if you know today's small [INAUDIBLE], cut it in four.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It will be for four people.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Now, when it was cut, it was eyed with eagle eyes, because everybody wanted to have the bit that looked a little bit longer as if his life depended on it.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And probably, it did.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Most-- many people ate it at once.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Maybe cut it in two.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "My father even managed to cut it-- we had sort of a spoon sharpened like a knife, the edge of a spoon, cut it even four small slices to go during the day.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I don't know if it helps.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I don't know which is the better system.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But that was the bread ration, and sometimes, a bit of margarine, which is the size of a sugar cube or two.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And black so-called coffee-- I'm not sure what it was.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But real coffee it wasn't.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But at one time, I thought I had diarrhea.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I thought, well-- anyway, at the sediments of the coffee, I sort of took it out with my fingers.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I added, and it filled the stomach a bit.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And also, by whatever reason, it cured my diarrhea.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Anyway, soon, it was-- at one time, as my thoughts go, sometimes I drop myself and speak.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "You know, go along with our thoughts.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "At one time, my other classmate, Max Spira, whom I managed to locate in America and rang recently to say another thank you, out of [INAUDIBLE] I met again once in Frankfurt after the war.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
